Project moves Eagle Ford natural gas to Gulf Coast markets. Pipeline begins at the existing KM Texas Pipeline (KMTP) compressor station near Freer, TX, and extends to the Tejas pipeline system near Sinton, TX. Said to be a critical supply link for impending growth from power generators, industrial customers and LNG exporters. Project is in conjunction with another by Dos Caminos, a Howard Energy Partners JV. Dos Caminos is constructing a 62-mile, 36-inch pipeline and other facilities in Webb County, TX, to the KMTP compressor station in Freer, TX.
